.Dd June 26, 2026
.Dt VSMBRINFO 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm vsmbrinfo
.Nd determines information about a Master Boot Record (MBR) volume system
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm vsmbrinfo
.Op Fl b Ar bytes_per_sector
.Op Fl hvV
.Ar source
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm vsmbrinfo
is a utility to determine information about a Master Boot Record (MBR) volume \
system
.Pp
.Nm vsmbrinfo
is part of the
.Nm libvsmbr
package.
.Nm libvsmbr
is a library to access the Master Boot Record (MBR) volume system format
.Pp
.Ar source
is the source image.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl b Ar bytes_per_sector
specify the number of bytes per sector (default is 512).
Use this to override the automatic bytes per sector detection
.It Fl h
shows this help
.It Fl v
verbose output to stderr
.It Fl V
print version
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
None
.Sh FILES
None
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal
# vsmbrinfo /dev/sda
vsmbrinfo 20260626
.sp
Master Boot Record (MBR) information:
	Disk identity		: 0x53f5a6ee (1408607982)
	Bytes per sector	: 512
	Number of partitions	: 2
.sp
Partition: 1
	Type			: 0x83 (Linux)
	Offset			: 512 (0x00000200)
	Size			: 179200
.sp
Partition: 2
	Type			: 0x83 (Linux)
	Offset			: 180224 (0x0002c000)
	Size			: 1294336
.sp
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Errors, verbose and debug output are printed to stderr when verbose output \
\-v is enabled.
Verbose and debug output are only printed when enabled at compilation.
